result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred judgment agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed. The defendant has not been convicted of the dismissed charges.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Ashley E Olson in court with attorney Ryan Drengler. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
11:13 a.m. case is called and appearances stated on the record.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.  Count #1 is amended and Count #2 is DRI.  W/h sentence. Probation - 12 mos. Pay costs; 30 hours community service; maintain absolute sobriety to alcohol and drugs; complete any programs as recommended by her agent; eligible for discharge; early discharge per agent; 
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of:  NC

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.  
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).  

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of Count #1 as charged, Count #2 is DRI.    Court withdraws its finding of guilt as this is not a conviction.

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Drengler makes sentencing arguments to the Court.  Defendant does not make a sentence.

BY THE COURT: 
In lieu of conviction the defendant is placed on 961.47 Deferred Judgment probation for a period of 12 months as a special provision for first time offender - no conviction entered
Condtions of probation
--Pay Court costs including Pay VW fees; filing fee and DNA surcharge
--30 hours of community service
--Maintain absolute sobriety.  Do not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid prescription and be taken according to the prescription. 
--Engage in Any counseling or program recommended by agent
--Allow early discharge if recommended by agent 

Atty Drengler asks for probation to transfer to Waupaca County
Court does allow the transfer

11:27 a.m. case is concluded.

State files Information.
Defendant received copy of information.
Defendant waives reading of information. 

NOT GUILTY Plea(s) entered.

Bond Continued.
